</ul></nav></section><section class="front-matter"><div class="ameta p font-secondary font-xs">
<hgroup><h1>Coffee, tea and decaffeinated coffee in relation to hepatocellular carcinoma in a European population: multi-centre, prospective cohort study</h1></hgroup><div class="cg p">
<a href='https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term="Bamia%20C"[Author]' class="usa-link" aria-describedby="id1"><span class="name western">Christina Bamia</span></a><div hidden="hidden" id="id1">
<h3><span class="name western">Christina Bamia</span></h3>
<div class="p">
<sup>1</sup>Department of Hygiene, Epidemiology and Medical Statistics, University of Athens Medical School, 115 27 Athens, Greece</div>
<div class="p">Find articles by <a href='https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/?term="Bamia%20C"[Author]' class="usa-link"><span class="name western">Christina Bamia</span></a>
</div>
